  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing the Monitoring and Reporting of Children&#x2019;s Rights Violations and Human Trafficking Victims Activity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Burundi):  .For five years, Burundi&apos;s classification under the Trafficking Victims Prevention Act of 2000 (TVPA) has remained at the Tier 3 level, with children included among the victims of trafficking. FY20 funds will support the follow-on to UNICEF&apos;s &quot;Enhancing the Monitoring and Reporting of Children&apos;s Rights Violations and Human Trafficking Victims Activity that developed a monitoring and reporting system to report abuse and violations against children, built a network of children rights monitors with at least one per commune, and achieved a decrease in incidences of violence against children in Burundi. Building on this, UNICEF is working to strengthen the capacity of the local network and is gradually transferring full implementation responsibilities to an association of national organizations with programs focusing on child rights-FENADEB (Federation Nationale des Associations Chargees de la Defense des Droits de l&apos;Enfant au Burundi)-through hands-on capacity building. In FY20, this activity adapted its training and interventions with FENADEB and the local monitors to capture cases in the new context where violence is reported in homes, schools, and communities, and to include documentation on trafficking in persons (TIP). UNICEF will also support data collection on children&apos;s rights violations with a focus on TIP to help the Government of Burundi achieve compliance with TVPA. These efforts will further Burundi&apos;s capacity to identify child victims of trafficking, put preventive measures in place to prevent further trafficking, and help in bringing cases against perpetrators so they can be prosecuted to the full extent of the law. The activity is aligned with the 2018-2027 Burundi National Development Plan and the Embassy&apos;s ICS Mission Objective of increased Burundian understanding of and transparent adherence to international human rights standards and the rule of law..</narrative>
  </description>
